 and properties need to be discussed. The second part is a contribution on nominalistic and platonistic views in mathematics, like the "indispensability argument" of W. v. O. Quine H. Putnam and the "makes no difference argument" of A. Baker. Not only in retrospect, the third part shows the problems of Mill, Frege's and the unity of mathematics and Descartes's contradictional conception of mathematical essences. Together, these articles give us a hint into the relationship between mathematics and world, that is, one of the central problems in philosophy of mathematics and philosophy of science.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aMathematicsxPhilosophyxElectronic books. 0aMathematicsxPhilosophy. 4aPhilosophie der Mathematik. 4aPhilosophie. 4amathematische Logik. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / General.2bisacsh1 aArana, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAzzouni, Jody, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBueno, Otávio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColyvan, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Rosa, Raffaella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEssler, Wilhelm K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMuntersbjorn, Madeline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPatterson, Douglas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeter, Georg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPreyer, Gerhard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRaley, Yvonne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVineberg, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/voc